org.simplity.kernel.data

Interface DataSheetIterator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CommonData.SheetIterator

    public interface DataSheetIterator
    In this iterator, we do not use a row explicitly, but implicitly by changing the default row of the sheet.
    Author:
    simplity.org

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void cancelIteration()
      should be called if the caller does not complete the iteration.
      boolean hasNext()
      peek operation.
      boolean moveToNextRow()
      make the next row as default in the data sheet.

    • Method Detail

      • hasNext

        boolean hasNext()
        peek operation. Does not change the state of the iterator
        Returns:
        true if a call to moveToNextRow() is going to return true or false.

      • moveToNextRow

        boolean moveToNextRow()
        make the next row as default in the data sheet. getField() will now return value from next row.
        Returns:
        true if the next row is made default. false if we have reached the end.

      • cancelIteration

        void cancelIteration()
        should be called if the caller does not complete the iteration. failing to do so will keep the sheet in an iterative state, there-by
